cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper discusses generative modeling of high dimensional data, specifically images, using adversarial learning. The paper also discusses the choice of divergence in GANs and its relation to structured prediction theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper discusses neural networks and optimization, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses statistical decision theory, cs.SD (Sound) is also a possible sub-category.
